8 Department of Corrections’ pretrial supervision program.
9 An act relating to creating a felony penalty for a violation of conditions of
10 release and to staff the pretrial supervision program
11 It is hereby enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Vermont:
12 Sec. 1. 13 V.S.A. § 7559 is amended to read:
13 § 7559. VIOLATIONS OF CONDITIONS OF RELEASE; FAILURE TO
14 APPEAR; WARRANTLESS ARREST
15 (a) The State’s Attorney may commence a prosecution for criminal
16 contempt under Rule 42 of the Vermont Rules of Criminal Procedure against a
17 person who violates a condition of release imposed under section 7554 of this
18 title. The maximum penalty that may be imposed under this section shall be a
19 fine of $1,000.00 or imprisonment for six months not more than three years, or
20 both.
