2 (c) A person who has been released pursuant to section 7554 of this title
3 with or without bail on condition that the person appear at a specified time and
4 place in connection with a prosecution for an offense and who without just
5 cause fails to appear shall be imprisoned not more than two three years or fined
6 not more than $5,000.00, or both.
7 * * *
8 Sec. 2. DEPARTMENT OF CORRECTIONS; POSITIONS;
9 APPROPRIATION
10 (a) To the extent funds are available, 12 new, permanent, classified Pretrial
11 Supervision Officers are created in fiscal year 2026 within the Department of
12 Corrections. In addition to any other duties deemed appropriate by the
13 Commissioner of Corrections, the Pretrial Supervision Officers shall supervise
14 Pretrial Supervision Program participants in accordance with 13 V.S.A.
15 § 7555.
16 (b) To the extent funds are available, two new, permanent, classified
17 administrative support positions are created in fiscal year 2026 within the
18 Department of Corrections. In addition to any other duties deemed appropriate
19 by the Commissioner of Corrections, the administrative support positions shall
20 assist in the administration and operation of the Pretrial Supervision Program
21 in accordance with 13 V.S.A. § 7555.
